OBJECTIVE: Hospice is a favored setting for dignity care. Studies on dignity 
dimension in end-of-life patients are growing. The Patient Dignity Inventory 
(PDI) is a tool that can lead to interesting information on dignity-related 
aspects of suffering. The study aimed to investigate dignity among end-of-life 
cancer patients, by examining the Italian version of the PDI factor structure 
and assessing the relationship between dignity and other patients' psychosocial 
