solution, accounting for 60% of the overall variance. The factors were labeled 
Psychological Distress, Social Support, Physical Symptoms and Dependency, 
Existential Distress, and Loss of Purpose/Meaning. Dignity assessment evidenced 
that self-blame coping style, emotional and physical well-being, and depression 
were the loss of dignity significant predictors (R2 = 0.605; p &lt; 
